    "body": "Python's package contains the following two lines:\n\n``` bash\nif spec.satisfies('@3:'):\n    config_args.append('--without-ensurepip')\n```\n\nWhich dates back to c65fd3a28968f549eed361d85f715caa4f8f6436. I was able to install python with pip after commenting out this line. Is this flag necessary, or could pip be a variant? Pip may be another package manager, but it's not superfluous.\n",
